# Fresher Basics

Required Format:

X.a What?
X.b Why?
X.c Reference 

1. Cloud/Internet
   
    A. Cloud is a huge server.We can store and access data from anywhere over the internet.There are 3types of cloud such as private,public,hybrid.It provides services such as IaaS, SaaS and PaaS to the clients.
    B. The reason was it provides flexibilty, cost reduction, reliability and powerful security. The user can virtually created their environment as per the requirement easily. 
    C.https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Cloud_computing

2. Client

    A.A Software or hardware requests the service provided by server called client.
    B.Client can use the services without client there is no possible to create the service.
    C.https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Client_(computing)

3. Server

   A.A computer can manage the resources,having business logic and database called server.
   B.Server can provide response depends upon the request.Without server we cannot able to handle more request at a time given from different clients.Any client can access it from anywhere at anytime.
   C.http://www.webopedia.com/TERM/S/server.html

4. HTTP

   A. HTTP is the underlying protocol used by the World Wide Web. HTTP defines how messages are formatted and transmitted over the internet and what actions the browsers should take in response to various commands.
   B.Both server and client need not use same language so http resolve this and it also provides proxy to resolve traffic over the network.
   C.http://timothyfitz.com/2009/02/12/why-http/

5. API

   A.It is a Software to software interface.It contains protocols and tool for developing applications.
   B.It has a requirement tat says how the two applications are communicated.
   C.http://money.howstuffworks.com/business-communications/how-to-leverage-an-api-for-conferencing1.htm

6. JSON

   A.It contains collection of string from that the developer can take the required information.It is a typeless notaion.
   B.It uses human readable format to transmit data.It is a language independant.
   C.http://www.json.org/

7. Databases
  
   A.It contains collection of tables to store the data permenantly.It also contains schemas,queries to fetch data efficiently.
   B.It stores the data in the specific format as developer design so easy to fetch the data according to the request by client.
   C.https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Database

8. Editor

   A.VM editor is used to write the code in an efficient way.It has 3 modes command mode,insert mode,command line mode.
   B.It access from command line.
   C.http://www.yolinux.com/TUTORIALS/LinuxTutorialAdvanced_vi.html
